{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Amend the Firearms Act to allow licensed defensive tasers for female adults 18+",
        "additional_details": "Violence against women, sexual offences, and abuse remains high in the UK, with police-recorded serious sexual offences exceeding 100,000 annually and low charge rates, leaving many feeling unsafe. We believe women and vulnerable adults need access to regulated, non-lethal defensive tools alongside legal protections. A targeted amendment with strict licensing and training could provide an additional, responsible option for personal safety without reducing public safety commitments.",
        "background": "Amend the Firearms Act 1968 to create a regulated licensing category for specialist defensive tasers, enabling lawful possession by female adults aged 18+ with mandatory training and safeguards, to support personal safety in the context of high levels of violence against women and vulnerable adults.",
